Job Portal Website – Full Project Structure & Database Plan
This document provides a complete structure and step-by-step plan for developing a Job Portal Website using React.js (Frontend), Node.js with Express (Backend), and MongoDB Atlas (Database).
The website will be fully responsive, ensuring a smooth user experience across all screen sizes — from small mobile devices to large desktop displays.
When designing the website’s folder structure:
The frontend should contain all front-end files, organized in well-named folders.
The backend should contain all back-end files, also placed in properly named folders for clarity and maintainability.
Additionally, create a separate folder named project_flow.
This folder will store all project documentation that will guide the entire development process.
Before starting any coding or development (through the terminal), you will always refer to this documentation. This ensures you won’t need to ask any questions during development — all necessary details will be clearly mentioned here.
The project_flow folder will include the following subfolders:
tables/
Contains text files describing all database tables (or collections).
Each file should specify the table name, fields, data types, and relationships between tables.
forms/
Contains text files related to all forms used in the admin panel.
Each file should include details like the form name, fields, and their functionality.
queries/
Stores all database queries or API request details as text files.
Each file should describe what the query does and when it’s used.
This structured documentation will help both of us maintain clear progress tracking.
Even if there’s a development gap or the project continues under a different AI subscription, anyone can easily understand the current stage of the project and continue development smoothly by referring to these files.
