1. ADMIN
Field Name	Type	Description
_id	ObjectId	Unique ID (default generated by MongoDB)
email	String	Admin email for login (unique, required)
password	String	Hashed password (required)
name	String	Admin name (required)
role	String	Role, default: 'admin'
createdAt	Date	Timestamp, default: current date
2. RECRUITERS
Field Name	Type	Description
_id	ObjectId	Unique ID
name	String	Recruiter or company name (required)
email	String	Login email (unique, required)
password	String	Hashed password (required)
address	String	Company address (optional)
contactno	String	Direct contact number (keep as string)

3. JOBS
Field Name	Type	Description
_id	ObjectId	Unique job ID
jobtitle	String	Job title (required)
experience	String	Experience required (e.g., '2+ years')
jobdescription	String	Job description (required)
postedBy	ObjectId	Recruiter/Admin reference
location	String	Job location (required)
salary	String	Salary info (formatted text like '₹50k/month')
category	String	Job type - 'Private', 'Government', 'Internship'
jobposteddate	Date	Post creation date (default: current date)
link	String	External or internal application link
status	String	Job status - 'pending', 'approved', 'rejected' (default: pending)
4. USERS
Field Name	Type	Description
_id	ObjectId	Unique user ID
name	String	Full name (required)
email	String	Login email (unique, required)
password	String	Hashed password (required)
contactno	String	Direct contact number (keep as string)

User Flow
1. User Registration
The user can sign up through the UserRegister.jsx page.
User details are stored in the users collection in MongoDB.
During registration, users provide their name, email, password, and contact number.
After successful registration, the user is redirected to the login page.

2. Login
The user logs in using their registered email and password.
Once logged in, the user is redirected to the home page to view available jobs.
If login credentials are invalid, an appropriate error message is displayed.

3. Home Page / Job List
The homepage displays a list of approved job postings fetched from the jobs collection.
Users can filter jobs by:
Location
Category (Private, Government, Internship)
Salary range
Even unregistered users (guests) can browse and view job listings to explore opportunities.
When an unregistered user clicks on “Apply,” a prompt to log in or register appears, encouraging them to create an account before applying.

4. Job Details
When a user clicks on a job, they can view the complete job description, including experience, location, category, and salary information.
Logged-in users can directly apply for the job from this page.
Unregistered users can still view job details but will need to log in or sign up to apply.

5. User Profile
Users can view and update their profile details including:   
Name
Email
Password
Contact number
Updates are reflected instantly in the users collection.
Optionally, users can delete their accounts or log out securely.

Recruiters Dashboard & Workflow
1. Recruiter Registration
The recruiter (company) fills out the registration form on the Recruiter Registration Page.
All details are stored in the recruiters collection in MongoDB.
The password is stored in hashed form for security.
After successful registration, the recruiter is redirected to the login page.

2. Recruiter Login
Recruiters log in using their registered email and password.
Upon successful login, the recruiter is redirected to their Dashboard.

3. Dashboard Overview
The Dashboard provides a summary of the company’s job activity, including:
Total Jobs Posted
Pending Jobs (awaiting admin approval)
Approved Jobs (visible to users on the site)
Rejected Jobs (declined by admin)
This section helps recruiters quickly track job status and performance.

4. Post a Job
Recruiters can create a new job posting through the “Post Job” form.
When a job is submitted, it is saved in the jobs collection with the status set to “pending”.
The Admin must review and approve the job before it becomes visible to users on the main site.
Recruiters can view this pending job in the “My Jobs” section until approval.

5. My Jobs
The “My Jobs” section lists all the jobs posted by the recruiter.
Each job displays its current status:
Pending
Approved
Rejected
Recruiters can edit or delete their job listings as needed.
When a job is edited, its status may be reset to “pending” for re-approval (recommended for content control).

6. Company Profile
Recruiters can manage their company information through the “Company Profile” section.
Editable fields include:
Company Name
Contact Number
Address
Password (with confirmation before update)
All updates are saved in the recruiters collection.
Password changes are securely hashed before being stored.
